 a few examples:</p> <p><strong>Alaskan King Salmon</strong></p> <p>Most fishermen who catch an <a href=\"http://www.fishalaskamagazine.com/fish/king_salmon.htm\"  title=\"Alaskan King Salmon\">Alaskan King Salmon</a> while on a luxury fishing trip to Alaska experience an unparalleled moment of pride. If you stay in an Alaskan fishing lodge near the Sitka Sound, your chances of catching Alaska&rsquo;s state fish are better than they would be anywhere else in the state.</p> <p><strong>Arctic Char</strong></p> <p>Most numerous along Alaska&rsquo;s western coast, this greenish-brown fish can sometimes be spotted in Alaska&rsquo;s southeastern waters. It is not uncommon for arctic char to weigh more than fifteen pounds!</p> <p><strong>Dolly Varden</strong></p> <p>If you are on a <a href=\"http://www.alaskafishingak.com/sitka/sitkafishing.htm\"  title=\"Fishing in Sitka, Alaska\">fishing trip in Southeastern Alaska,</a> you are almost guaranteed to see Dolly Varden, a type of fish that is hardly distinguishable from the arctic char. The Dolly Varden is smaller and lighter, usually with silvery sides.</p> <p><strong>Rainbow Trout</strong></p> <p>A favorite catch among fishermen and foodies alike, rainbow trout can be a struggle to wrestle with&mdash;weighing up to forty pounds&mdash;and a delight to eat. These trout are abundant in the freshwater rivers of Alaska&rsquo;s southeastern coast.</p> <p><strong>Copper Rockfish</strong></p> <p>The Copper Rockfish, with its multi-colored scales and its spiky fins, is one of the most intriguing fish in Alaska. Competitive fishermen and thrill-seekers are intrigued by the rockfish because it is the only venomous sport fish in Alaska. This does not make them inedible. In fact, many individuals who do not care for fishy tastes enjoy the tender white meat of this spiny fish.</p> <p>If you want to rest in style after a day of <a href=\"http://www.talonlodge.com/fishing/\"  title=\"Talon Lodge: Fishing\">luxury fishing</a>, Sitka&rsquo;s <a href=\"http://www.talonlodge.com/\"  title=\"Talon Lodge Website\">Talon Lodge</a> may be the perfect place for you to stay on your next Alaskan fishing trip. With a full service spa, a full gourmet kitchen, and a range of accommodation options to choose from, this fishing resort has something for everyone. Look through our beautiful <a href=\"http://www.talonlodge.com/gallery/\"  title=\"Talon Lodge Photo Gallery\">photo gallery</a> and then call us today at (888) 763-5630 to book a room!</p>\n<p class=\"photos\">\n<img src=\'http://rc-images.s3.amazonaws.com/7f6a3dc1-3465-493f-80e6-ab1f4a9be23d/media/163699/medium/163699.PNG?ver=1&gen=1\' /><br />\n</p>\n<p class=\"tags\">More from Talon Lodge: <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaska+Fishing+Lodge\'>Alaska Fishing Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaska+Fishing+Sitka\'>Alaska Fishing Sitka</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Luxury+Alaskan+Fishing+Lodge\'>Luxury Alaskan Fishing Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Talon+Lodge\'>Talon Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaskan+Vacations\'>Alaskan Vacations</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Talon+Lodge+Alaska\'>Talon Lodge Alaska</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Sitka+Fishing+Lodges\'>Sitka Fishing Lodges</a></p>\n<a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/163668/2011/06/28/what-type-of-fish-can-you-catch-in-alaska.html#comments\'>0 comments</a> | <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/163668/2011/06/28/what-type-of-fish-can-you-catch-in-alaska.html?commentFocus=true#comments\'>Leave a comment &raquo;</a>\n<br />','What Type of Fish Can You Catch in Alaska?','When an experienced fisher hears &ldquo;Alaska,&rdquo; salmon is usually the first fish that comes to mind. Alaskan salmon are certainly special, but Alaska is home to many species of fish that most fishermen or fisherwomen would be thrilled to catch. ...','publish','closed','closed','','what-type-of-fish-can-you-catch-in-alaska','','','2011-06-28 14:33:53','2011-06-28 14:33:53','',0,'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/163668/2011/06/28/what-type-of-fish-can-you-catch-in-alaska.html',0,'post','',0),(27,3,'2011-06-22 04:24:03','2011-06-22 04:24:03','<p class=\"photos\">\n<img src=\'http://rc-images.s3.amazonaws.com/7f6a3dc1-3465-493f-80e6-ab1f4a9be23d/media/158447/medium/158447.PNG?ver=1&gen=1\' /><br />\n</p><p>Are you planning a vacation to Alaska? If so, this free app can save you hours of research. With detailed information regarding all of Alaska&rsquo;s best places to visit, including photos or videos for most of them, the <a href=\"http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/the-alaska-app/id385577797?mt=8\"  title=\"iTunes Alaska App\">Alaska App</a> is useful even to travel veterans and Alaskan natives.</p> <p>From the comfort of your home sofa or the convenience of your office chair, plan the details of your next Alaskan adventure from start to finish. Whether you want hiking, fishing, camping, or hunting recommendations, or are looking to book your dream Alaskan cruise, this app is an indispensable planning tool.</p> <p>If you are looking to fish in Alaska&rsquo;s rich southeastern waters, consider staying at <a href=\"http://www.talonlodge.com/\"  title=\"Talon Lodge Website\">Talon Lodge</a> in Sitka. As one of Alaska&rsquo;s most luxurious fishing resorts, we offer full service spa amenities, fine dining, and great entertainment and sport options that everyone in your party will enjoy. Visit our website or call (888) 763-5630 for more information today!</p>\n<p class=\"photos\">\n<img src=\'http://rc-images.s3.amazonaws.com/7f6a3dc1-3465-493f-80e6-ab1f4a9be23d/media/158448/medium/158448.PNG?ver=1&gen=1\' /><br />\n<img src=\'http://rc-images.s3.amazonaws.com/7f6a3dc1-3465-493f-80e6-ab1f4a9be23d/media/158449/medium/158449.PNG?ver=1&gen=1\' /><br />\n<img src=\'http://rc-images.s3.amazonaws.com/7f6a3dc1-3465-493f-80e6-ab1f4a9be23d/media/158450/medium/158450.PNG?ver=1&gen=1\' /><br />\n<img src=\'http://rc-images.s3.amazonaws.com/7f6a3dc1-3465-493f-80e6-ab1f4a9be23d/media/158451/medium/158451.PNG?ver=1&gen=1\' /><br />\n<img src=\'http://rc-images.s3.amazonaws.com/7f6a3dc1-3465-493f-80e6-ab1f4a9be23d/media/158452/medium/158452.PNG?ver=1&gen=1\' /><br />\n</p>\n<p class=\"tags\">More from Talon Lodge: <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaska+Fishing+Lodge\'>Alaska Fishing Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaska+Fishing+Sitka\'>Alaska Fishing Sitka</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Luxury+Alaskan+Fishing+Lodge\'>Luxury Alaskan Fishing Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Talon+Lodge\'>Talon Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaskan+Vacations\'>Alaskan Vacations</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Talon+Lodge+Alaska\'>Talon Lodge Alaska</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Sitka+Fishing+Lodges\'>Sitka Fishing Lodges</a></p>\n<a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/158446/2011/06/22/itunes-app-the-alaska-app.html#comments\'>0 comments</a> | <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/158446/2011/06/22/itunes-app-the-alaska-app.html?commentFocus=true#comments\'>Leave a comment &raquo;</a>\n<br />','iTunes App: The Alaska App','\n\nAre you planning a vacation to Alaska? If so, this free app can save you hours of research. With detailed information regarding all of Alaska&rsquo;s best places to visit, including photos or videos for most of them, the Alaska App is useful even to ...','publish','closed','closed','','itunes-app-the-alaska-app','','','2011-06-22 04:24:03','2011-06-22 04:24:03','',0,'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/158446/2011/06/22/itunes-app-the-alaska-app.html',0,'post','',0),(28,3,'2011-06-13 19:41:40','2011-06-13 19:41:40','<p>Every fisherman dreams of fishing for salmon in Alaska&rsquo;s cool, clean rivers or the Sitka Sound. If you are preparing for the Alaskan fishing trip you have always dreamed of, keep the following <a href=\"http://www.fishabout.com/article/Packing_for_Your_Next_Fishing_Trip\"  title=\"Packing for Your Next Fishing Trip\">packing tips</a> in mind as you prepare to set off for your fishing lodge.</p> <p><strong>Bring waterproof everything.</strong></p> <p>The purpose of your trip is to fish. You are going to get wet, and the water will be cold. Bring at least one or two articles of waterproof clothing, including shoes, to cover every part of your body. Doing this will help you stay warm and dry. Bring extra socks, as cold and wet feet are uncomfortable and increase your risk of frostbite.<strong><br /><br /></strong></p> <p><strong>Service and pack your fishing gear.</strong></p> <p>If any of your fishing gear is in need of maintenance, have it serviced before your Alaska fishing trip. You may also want to bring a small tool kit to make any necessary repairs in the field.</p> <p><strong>Pack enough layers.</strong></p> <p>Days can be cool in Alaska and nights are usually chilly, even in summer. However, the Sitka sun can sometimes make the temperature feel warmer than it actually is in the middle of the day. Plan on wearing easily-removable layers so that you can be comfortable both when you set off early in the morning and during the middle of the day when the sun is at its highest point.</p> <p><strong>Consider your lodgings.</strong></p> <p>Your packing list will be different if you stay at a luxury fishing lodge than it will be if you are camping for two weeks. Think about your lodging when you pack clothes, toiletries, and supplies.</p> <p><strong>Don&rsquo;t forget bug spray!</strong></p> <p>Alaska is a notorious <a href=\"http://www.alaskacenters.gov/pests.cfm\"  title=\"Alaska\'s Pests\">insect haven</a> during the summertime. Be considerate of the environment and bring a pump or cream, as they are more environmentally friendly than aerosol sprays. Depending on where you are sleeping, you may also want to consider packing a mosquito net.</p> <p>To start planning your luxurious Alaska fishing adventure, check out the <a href=\"http://www.talonlodge.com/\"  title=\"Talon Lodge Website\">Talon Lodge</a>, Sitka&rsquo;s premier fishing resort. Call us at (888) 763-5630 to find out more!</p>\n<p class=\"tags\">More from Talon Lodge: <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaska+Fishing+Lodge\'>Alaska Fishing Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaska+Fishing+Sitka\'>Alaska Fishing Sitka</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Luxury+Alaskan+Fishing+Lodge\'>Luxury Alaskan Fishing Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Talon+Lodge\'>Talon Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaskan+Vacations\'>Alaskan Vacations</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Talon+Lodge+Alaska\'>Talon Lodge Alaska</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Sitka+Fishing+Lodges\'>Sitka Fishing Lodges</a></p>\n<a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/149606/2011/06/15/tips-for-packing-for-your-alaskan-fishing-trip.html#comments\'>0 comments</a> | <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/149606/2011/06/15/tips-for-packing-for-your-alaskan-fishing-trip.html?commentFocus=true#comments\'>Leave a comment &raquo;</a>\n<br />','Tips for Packing for Your Alaskan Fishing Trip','Every fisherman dreams of fishing for salmon in Alaska&rsquo;s cool, clean rivers or the Sitka Sound. If you are preparing for the Alaskan fishing trip you have always dreamed of, keep the following packing tips in mind as you prepare t