known as the Orca, is one of the most famous of all the <a href=\"http://www.fakr.noaa.gov/protectedresources/mmv/guide.htm\"  title=\"Viewing Humpback Whales\">marine mammals</a>. Try to catch sight of these magical creatures as they roll through the waves near your Alaska fishing resort. Watching a whale in its natural habitat is a moving experience, especially if it&rsquo;s a beautiful Orca. The black and white of their bodies slices through the blue/grey waters, giving you a glimpse that will leave you breathless.</p> <p><strong>The Bald Eagle</strong></p> <p>With more than 30,000 bald eagles in the state, Alaska is the perfect place to see this national emblem in person. Watch them in their natural habitats as they fly along the Alaskan waterways. Don&rsquo;t forget to occasionally look toward the sky as you&rsquo;re sitting by the water of your Alaska fishing lodge. Chances are that you&rsquo;ll see a bald eagle swoop through the sky.</p> <p><strong>Grizzly Bears</strong></p> <p>Alaska has 98% of the United States of America&rsquo;s grizzly population living within its borders. Only in Alaska do you have the opportunity to see such <a href=\"http://www.alaskascenes.com/wildlife.html\"  title=\"Wildlife in Alaska\">wildlife</a> in its natural habitat, unspoiled by relocation or other issues that come with building and city development.  Of course, you&rsquo;ll want to keep your distance from these powerful animals.</p> <p><strong>Halibut and Salmon</strong></p> <p>Your luxury fishing in Alaska won&rsquo;t be complete without an opportunity to catch some halibut and salmon in beautiful waters. Ask your fishing guide about the best places to catch these fish.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Come and see the diverse wildlife of Alaska at the <a href=\"http://www.talonlodge.com/about/wildlife.asp\"  title=\"Talon Lodge: Wildlife\">Talon Lodge.</a> If you want to experience <a href=\"http://www.talonlodge.com/fishing/\"  title=\"Talon Lodge: Fishing\">luxury fishing in Sitka</a> while you enjoy precious wildlife, then we&rsquo;re the place for you.  At Talon Lodge, you can have the best and most relaxing <a href=\"http://www.talonlodge.com/difference/\"  title=\"Talon Lodge: The Difference\">Alaskan fishing trip</a> of your life. Call today to reserve your spot.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"photos\">\n<img src=\'http://rc-images.s3.amazonaws.com/7f6a3dc1-3465-493f-80e6-ab1f4a9be23d/media/125782/medium/125782.PNG?ver=1&gen=1\' /><br />\n</p>\n<p class=\"tags\">More from Talon Lodge: <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Talon+Lodge\'>Talon Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaskan+Vacations\'>Alaskan Vacations</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Talon+Lodge+Alaska\'>Talon Lodge Alaska</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Luxury+Alaskan+Fishing+Lodge\'>Luxury Alaskan Fishing Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaska+Fishing+Sitka\'>Alaska Fishing Sitka</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Sitka+Fishing+Lodges\'>Sitka Fishing Lodges</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaska+Fishing+Lodge\'>Alaska Fishing Lodge</a></p>\n<a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/125783/2011/05/26/a-look-at-alaskas-wildlife.html#comments\'>1 comments</a> | <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/125783/2011/05/26/a-look-at-alaskas-wildlife.html?commentFocus=true#comments\'>Leave a comment &raquo;</a>\n<br />','A Look at Alaska\'s Wildlife','Alaska has one of the most beautiful and unique natural landscapes in the world. The next time you&rsquo;re on an Alaskan fishing trip, keep your eyes open for these majestic creatures that make up the state&rsquo;s diverse wildlife. Killer Whales The ...','inherit','open','open','','35-revision','','','2011-05-16 14:52:37','2011-05-16 14:52:37','',35,'http://wordpress.talonlodge.com/?p=45',0,'revision','',0),(46,3,'2011-07-07 00:51:49','2011-07-07 00:51:49','<p class=\"photos\">\n<img src=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/photos/medium/170955.PNG?ver=0&gen=1\' /><br />\n</p><p>Congratulations Glen on this 41lb King Salmon.&nbsp; It was close, but this King beat out the competition for the largest King in June 2011.</p>\n<p class=\"tags\">More from Talon Lodge: <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaska+Fishing+Sitka\'>Alaska Fishing Sitka</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaskan+Vacations\'>Alaskan Vacations</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Sitka+Fishing+Lodges\'>Sitka Fishing Lodges</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Luxury+Alaskan+Fishing+Lodge\'>Luxury Alaskan Fishing Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Talon+Lodge\'>Talon Lodge</a></p>\n<a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/170956/2011/07/06/june-king-salmon-leader!.html#comments\'>0 comments</a> | <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/170956/2011/07/06/june-king-salmon-leader!.html?commentFocus=true#comments\'>Leave a comment &raquo;</a>\n<br />','June King Salmon Leader!','\n\nCongratulations Glen on this 41lb King Salmon.&nbsp; It was close, but this King beat out the competition for the largest King in June 2011.\nMore from Talon Lodge: Alaska Fishing Sitka, Alaskan Vacations, Sitka Fishing Lodges, Luxury Alaskan Fishing ...','inherit','open','open','','june-king-salmon-leader-2','','','2011-07-07 00:56:06','2011-07-07 00:56:06','',0,'http://wordpress.talonlodge.com/?p=46',0,'post','',0),(47,3,'2011-06-28 14:33:53','2011-06-28 14:33:53','<p>When an experienced fisher hears &ldquo;Alaska,&rdquo; salmon is usually the first fish that comes to mind. Alaskan salmon are certainly special, but Alaska is home to many species of fish that most fishermen or fisherwomen would be thrilled to catch. Here are just a few examples:</p> <p><strong>Alaskan King Salmon</strong></p> <p>Most fishermen who catch an <a href=\"http://www.fishalaskamagazine.com/fish/king_salmon.htm\"  title=\"Alaskan King Salmon\">Alaskan King Salmon</a> while on a luxury fishing trip to Alaska experience an unparalleled moment of pride. If you stay in an Alaskan fishing lodge near the Sitka Sound, your chances of catching Alaska&rsquo;s state fish are better than they would be anywhere else in the state.</p> <p><strong>Arctic Char</strong></p> <p>Most numerous along Alaska&rsquo;s western coast, this greenish-brown fish can sometimes be spotted in Alaska&rsquo;s southeastern waters. It is not uncommon for arctic char to weigh more than fifteen pounds!</p> <p><strong>Dolly Varden</strong></p> <p>If you are on a <a href=\"http://www.alaskafishingak.com/sitka/sitkafishing.htm\"  title=\"Fishing in Sitka, Alaska\">fishing trip in Southeastern Alaska,</a> you are almost guaranteed to see Dolly Varden, a type of fish that is hardly distinguishable from the arctic char. The Dolly Varden is smaller and lighter, usually with silvery sides.</p> <p><strong>Rainbow Trout</strong></p> <p>A favorite catch among fishermen and foodies alike, rainbow trout can be a struggle to wrestle with&mdash;weighing up to forty pounds&mdash;and a delight to eat. These trout are abundant in the freshwater rivers of Alaska&rsquo;s southeastern coast.</p> <p><strong>Copper Rockfish</strong></p> <p>The Copper Rockfish, with its multi-colored scales and its spiky fins, is one of the most intriguing fish in Alaska. Competitive fishermen and thrill-seekers are intrigued by the rockfish because it is the only venomous sport fish in Alaska. This does not make them inedible. In fact, many individuals who do not care for fishy tastes enjoy the tender white meat of this spiny fish.</p> <p>If you want to rest in style after a day of <a href=\"http://www.talonlodge.com/fishing/\"  title=\"Talon Lodge: Fishing\">luxury fishing</a>, Si