ut and the weather was spectacular.</p> <p>NFL Great Larry Csonka and our NAPA guests enjoyed lounging on the deck overlooking our private beach, massages at the spa pavilion, a wonderful 5-course gourmet meal and an evening of horseshoes and laughter.</p>\n<p class=\"photos\">\n<img src=\'http://rc-images.s3.amazonaws.com/7f6a3dc1-3465-493f-80e6-ab1f4a9be23d/media/133862/medium/133862.PNG?ver=1&gen=1\' /><br />\n</p>\n<p class=\"tags\">More from Talon Lodge: <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Talon+Lodge\'>Talon Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Luxury+Alaskan+Fishing+Lodge\'>Luxury Alaskan Fishing Lodge</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaskan+Vacations\'>Alaskan Vacations</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Alaska+Fishing+Sitka\'>Alaska Fishing Sitka</a>, <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/search/tag/Sitka+Fishing+Lodges\'>Sitka Fishing Lodges</a></p>\n<a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/133863/2011/05/25/after-fishing-at-talon-lodge.html#comments\'>0 comments</a> | <a href=\'http://www.luxuryalaskanfishinglodge.com/133863/2011/05/25/after-fishing-at-talon-lodge.html?commentFocus=true#comments\'>Leave a comment &raquo;</a>\n<br />','After Fishing at Talon Lodge','We can&rsquo;t guarantee that every day will be as nice as this photo, but yesterday was a pretty special day at Talon Lodge. Not only did we have a great day of Alaska fishing, but the sun was out and the weather was spectacular. NFL Great Larry Csonk...','inherit','open','open','','33-revision-3','','','2011-05-25 14:16:00','2011-05-25 14:16:00','',33,'http://wordpress.talonlodge.com/?p=61',0,'revision','',0),(62,3,'2011-05-16 14:52:37','2011-05-16 14:52:37','<p>Alaska has one of the most beautiful and unique natural landscapes in the world. The next time you&rsquo;re on an Alaskan fishing trip, keep your eyes open for these majestic creatures that make up the state&rsquo;s diverse wildlife.</p> <p><strong>Killer Whales</strong></p> <p>The Killer Whale, also known as the Orca, is one of the most famous of all the <a href=\"http://www.fakr.noaa.gov/protectedresources/mmv/guide.htm\"  title=\"Viewing Humpback Whales\">marine mammals</a>. Try to catch sight of these magical creatures as they roll through the waves near your Alaska fishing resort. Watching a whale in its natural habitat is a moving experience, especially if it&rsquo;s a beautiful Orca. The black and white of their bodies slices through the blue/grey waters, giving you a glimpse that will leave you breathless.</p> <p><strong>The Bald Eagle</strong></p> <p>With more than 30,000 bald eagles in the state, Alaska is the perfect place to see this national emblem in person. Watch them in their natural habitats as they fly along the Alaskan waterways. Don&rsquo;t forget to occasionally look toward the sky as you&rsquo;re sitting by the water of your Alaska fishing lodge. Chances are that you&rsquo;ll see a bald eagle swoop through the sky.</p> <p><strong>Grizzly Bears</strong></p> <p>Alaska has 98% of the United States of America&rsquo;s grizzly population living within its borders. Only in Alaska do you have the opportunity to see such <a href=\"http://www.alaskascenes.com/wildlife.html\"  title=\"Wildlife in Alaska\">wildlife</a> in its natural habitat, unspoiled by relocation or other issues that come with building and city development.  Of course, you&rsquo;ll want to keep your distance from these powerful animals.</p> <p><strong>Halibut and Salmon</strong></p> <p>Your luxury fishing in Alaska won&rsquo;t be complete without an opportunity to catch some halibut and salmon in beautiful waters. Ask your fishing guide about the best places to catch these fish.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Come and see the diverse wildlife of Alaska at the <a href=\"http://www.talonlodge.com/about/wildlife.asp\"  title=\"Talon Lodge: Wildlife\">Talon Lodge.</a> If you want 