his beautiful city, with a population under 9,000 residents, offers some of the state&rsquo;s most beautiful views. Sitka is also home to some of <strong><a href=\"http://traveltips.usatoday.com/information-hiking-alaska-10168.html\"  title=\"Alaska\'s Top Fishing Lodges\">Alaska&rsquo;s top fishing lodges</a></strong>, offering tourists stunning hiking and kayaking opportunities. These tips will help you plan your adventures:</p> <ul> <li><strong>Ask about hiking and kayaking guides.</strong> </li> </ul> <p>Alaskan fishing lodges don&rsquo;t just give you access to great land, great waters, and great fish; they also give you the tools you need to make the most of your experience. Ask the staff about guides or scheduled trips. They can plan a day of hiking for you and provide you with information on where to go and what you&rsquo;ll see there. An experienced captain can help you find your way through the majestic waters.</p> <ul> <li><strong>Dress appropriately.</strong></li> </ul> <p>It&rsquo;s important to wear the right type and amount of clothing when hiking in Alaska. You can prepare yourself for the weather by adding layers. Start with long underwear, followed by warm, water-resistant pants and a sweater, topped with a warm winter jacket. Find lightweight hikers or hiking boots to keep your feet more comfortable during the hike.</p> <ul> <li><strong>Bring a camera!</strong></li> </ul> <p>After your hiking or kayaking adventure is planned, you&rsquo;ll want to make sure to pack your camera. The scenery of Sitka is sure to leave you breathless. While the views are unforgettable, a camera will help you share your <strong><a href=\"http://www.sitka.org/explore/wildlife/\"  title=\"Alaskan Vacation\">Alaskan vacation</a></strong> adventures with your loved ones back home and bring you long-lasting memories. When you stop to take a break during your hike, grab your camera and take a few pictures for keepsakes!</p> <p>At <strong><a href=\"http://www.talonlodge.com/\"